OL,3,C'The war against lanyards': Starmer
OL,4,Cmocks PM over 'ban' on rainbow lanyards
OL,6,F"Working for the civil service is all
OL,7,Fabout leaving your political views at
OL,8,Fthe building entrance, trying to
OL,9,Fintroduce them by the backdoor via
OL,10,Flanyards should not happen."
OL,12,FSince the comments by Ms McVey, new
OL,13,Fcivil service guidance has come out
OL,14,Fwhich doesn't reference any ban on
OL,15,Frainbow lanyards. Despite this, the PM
OL,16,Fand a number of cabinet ministers have
OL,17,Fdefended the thinking behind Ms
OL,18,FMcVey's comments.
