OL,3,C'The war against lanyards': Starmer
OL,4,Cmocks PM over 'ban' on rainbow lanyards
OL,6,FThe Times newspaper reported on
OL,7,FWednesday that a Tory MP had observed
OL,8,F"a lot more people in Parliament than
OL,9,Fusual wearing rainbow lanyards in a
OL,10,Fshow of solidarity."
OL,12,FA refresh of the guidance provided to
OL,13,Fon their duty to remain impartial was
OL,14,Fpublished on Tuesday night, which said
OL,15,Fthey must "always be guided by the
OL,16,Fcore values of objectivity and
OL,17,Fimpartiality set out in the Civil
OL,18,FService code when carrying out work in
OL,19,Fdiversity and inclusion", but made no
OL,20,Fdirect reference to staff lanyards.
